explain 
select /*+parallel(2) leading(stu, teacher) use_hash(teacher) px_join_filter(teacher)*/ 
sum (cls)
from stu, teacher
where 
tid = sid
and
(subject in ('KY') and cls between 0 and 2000  
or subject in ('WI', 'MO', 'WV')
);
Query Plan
=========================================================================
|ID|OPERATOR                             |NAME    |EST.ROWS|EST.TIME(us)|
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
|0 |SCALAR GROUP BY                      |        |1       |16          |
|1 |└─PX COORDINATOR                     |        |1       |16          |
|2 |  └─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR               |:EX10001|1       |16          |
|3 |    └─MERGE GROUP BY                 |        |1       |16          |
|4 |      └─HASH JOIN                    |        |1       |16          |
|5 |        ├─JOIN FILTER CREATE         |:RF0000 |1       |7           |
|6 |        │ └─PX PARTITION ITERATOR    |        |1       |7           |
|7 |        │   └─TABLE FULL SCAN        |stu     |1       |7           |
|8 |        └─EXCHANGE IN DISTR          |        |1       |9           |
|9 |          └─EXCHANGE OUT DISTR (PKEY)|:EX10000|1       |9           |
|10|            └─JOIN FILTER USE        |:RF0000 |1       |9           |
|11|              └─PX BLOCK ITERATOR    |        |1       |9           |
|12|                └─TABLE FULL SCAN    |teacher |1       |9           |
=========================================================================
